==English==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|bright}}, from {{inh|en|ang|bryht}}, a metathetic variant of {{m|ang|byrht}}, {{m|ang|beorht}}, {{m|ang|berht||bright}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*berht}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*berhtaz}} (compare {{cog|sco|bricht}}, {{cog|nl|brecht}} {{qualifier|in personal names}}, {{cog|no|bjart}}, {{cog|is|bjartur|t=bright}}), from pre-Celtic/Germanic {{m|ine-pro|*bʰerHgto}} (compare {{cog|cy|berth||beautiful}}), from {{der|en|ine-pro|*bʰereg-||to gleam, whiten}}. 

Compare {{cog|mga|brafad||blink of an eye}}, {{cog|lt|brekšta||to dawn}}, {{cog|ru|брезг||dawn, daybreak}}, {{cog|sq|bardhë||white}}, {{cog|fa|برازیدن|tr=barâzidan}}, {{cog|sa|भ्राजते|tr=bhrájate}}.

